Paul R. Rudder, 56 years old, was named senior vice president of operations at this railroad holding company, effective Sunday.
He will become executive vice president of operations March 1, when Edward B. Burwell, 62, takes early retirement.
Mr. Rudder will be succeeded as vice president of engineering by Charles M. Irvin, 51, who is now vice president of transportation.
Stephen C. Tobias, 44, currently general manager of the Western region, will become vice president of transportation Sunday. 

